						               													<description>&amp;quot;Spiele Minis&amp;quot; is a series of small surprise boxes (i.e., you don't know what you get) from Ravensburger. They are meant to be carry-on or gifts, suitable for children (&amp;quot;Mitbringspiel&amp;quot;). Some of the cubes contain actual games, others contain magic tricks, puzzles etc.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;20 pieces of cloth are placed in the middle of the table. Each player has a clothes line.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On your turn you must throw a die and you get a cloth in the corresponding color, which you hang on your clothes line. If no cloths of that color are left then you receive nothing.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If you throw a sun you must take a sunbeam and place it aside (there are 6). If the sun in the die is shining you can chose any cloth from the middle, but if its unhappy you must return one of yours to the middle (or one of an opponent if you don&amp;rsquo;t have any left).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends when the sixth sunbeam is taken. The player with more cloth on his clothes line wins!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
